HEADWORD: Lenni-Lenape
<hw>Len`ni-Len*a"pe</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧n`n⟦icr⟧-l⟦ecr⟧n*⟦aum⟧"p⟦asl⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A general name for a group
of Algonquin tribes which formerly occupied the coast region of North
America from Connecticut to Virginia. They included the Mohicans,
Delawares, Shawnees, and several other tribes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

